author: CNN
description: Saying that "it was probably the most productive day we have had on this issue, maybe in the entirety of our engagement, but certainly in a very long time," Secretary of State Marco Rubio provided an update on the Ukraine peace talks in Geneva, Switzerland, adding that the sticking points on the Trump administration’s Russia-Ukraine peace proposal are “not insurmountable.” Ukraine has also said the delegations made good progress. It remains to be seen if Moscow would sign on to the terms being hammered out between Washington and Kyiv. Trump’s original 28-point peace plan had been widely considered favorable to Russia and was met with concern from European allies. #CNN #News
title: Secretary Rubio speaks about discussions with Ukraine

author: CNN
description: CNN's Jake Tapper speaks with Sen. Bill Cassidy (R-LA), who is a medical doctor, on HHS Secretary Robert F. Kennedy Jr.'s recent changes to the CDC website, Affordable Care Act reform and vaccine safety. #CNN #News
title: Sen. Cassidy reacts to RFK Jr.'s changes to the CDC website

author: CNN
description: In a wide-ranging interview with CNN's Jake Tapper, Rep. Jasmine Crockett (D-TX) discusses Rep. Marjorie Taylor Greene's resignation announcement, the Epstein files investigation, her potential 2026 Senate run, and more. #CNN #News
title: One-on-one with Rep. Jasmine Crockett

author: CNN
description: In an exclusive interview, CNN's Omar Jimenez speaks with Marimar Martinez, a United States citizen who was accused of ramming the vehicle of a Customs and Border Protection agent in Chicago before he shot her several times. A judge dismissed charges against Martinez after a reversal by federal prosecutors in one of the most high-profile cases connected to Operation Midway Blitz in Chicago. #CNN #News
title: CNN speaks with woman shot by Border Patrol five times

author: CNN
description:
Tatiana Schlossberg, the 35-year-old granddaughter of President John F. Kennedy, has revealed that she has terminal acute myeloid leukemia. Diagnosed shortly after giving birth, Schlossberg says doctors have told her she likely has less than a year to live.

#CNN #News
title: JFK's granddaughter reveals terminal cancer diagnosis

author: CNN
description:
GOP leaders in Washington are ramping up pressure on Republican Rep. Wesley Hunt to drop out of the Texas Senate race, warning that his candidacy could cost their party tens of millions of dollars and even upend their midterm map. But a defiant Hunt told CNN's Manu Raju in an exclusive interview that he is “absolutely” staying in the heated three-way race against long-time incumbent Sen. John Cornyn and firebrand Texas Attorney General Ken Paxton, even as senior Republicans accuse him of being a “spoiler” in the race that is now all but certain to lead to a costly runoff.

Manu Raju discusses with his "Inside Politics" panel: Anna Palmer of Punchbowl News, CNN Washington bureau chief and political director David Chalian and AP White House reporter Seung Min Kim. #CNN #News
title: Messy Texas Senate primary puts Trump & Republicans in a bind

author: CNN
description:
CNN's Victor Blackwell spoke with a mom who says a hospital in Indiana discharged her while she was in labor, forcing her to give birth on the side of the road. The hospital she visited, Franciscan Health Crown Point, says the nurse and doctor responsible for her care are no longer employed.

#CNN #News #Indiana
title: Parents speak out after hospital discharged mom while in labor

author: CNN
description:
President Donald Trump has long had an ironclad grip on his party, but the GOP revolt over the release of the Epstein files, the abrupt resignation of onetime MAGA loyalist Rep. Marjorie Taylor Greene (R-GA) and falling poll numbers raise the question of how long Republicans will continue to toe the line.

CNN's Manu Raju breaks down the news with his "Inside Politics" panel: Anna Palmer of Punchbowl News, CNN Washington bureau chief and political director David Chalian and AP White House reporter Seung Min Kim. #CNN #News
title: Trump at tipping point as polls worsen and GOP breaks ranks

author: CNN
description: Crispy skin, along with a bed of veggies and caramelized fruit, will make this easier turkey swap a highlight of your Thanksgiving table, according to Suzy Karadsheh, a New York Times best-selling author and founder of The Mediterranean Dish. #thanksgiving #mediterranean #mediterraneanfood #turkey #thanksgivinghacks #cnn
title: Go for turkey breast for Thanksgiving

author: CNN
description:
Top US diplomats will hold talks with Ukrainian and European officials in Geneva today as the clock ticks on President Donald Trump’s Thursday deadline for Kyiv to accept his 28-point proposal to end the war with Russia.  Trump indicated yesterday the proposal on the table is not his “final offer.” As it stands, the plan is widely considered favorable to Russia. European leaders say the framework needs “additional work” as they try to reestablish a role in the talks.

CNN's Kevin Liptak reports from the White House, and Victor Blackwell speaks with CNN global affairs analyst Kimberly Dozier. #CNN #News
title: Trump: If Zelensky doesn't accept peace deal 'he can fight his little heart out'

author: CNN
description: CNN speaks to Ukrainians about their reaction to a US proposal for ending the war with Russia. Trump has given Ukrainian President Volodymyr Zelensky less than a week to accept the plan. But Trump said Saturday the plan is not his final offer to end the war.
title: Ukrainians express fears over US-backed peace plan

description: CNN’s Gloria Pazmino speaks to NYC residents about their reactions to the Oval Office meeting between New York City Mayor-elect Zohran Mamdani and President Donald Trump. Both politicians are from New York and have criticized each other in the past. #nyc #trump #cnn
title: NYC residents react to Mamdani-Trump meeting
